Across {= holder_or_source_family =}+ distinct holder/source families, identify {= archive_holding =}+ archive holdings per holder/source family as having material Persian/Farsi recorded-audio components; for each holding, cover each of the {= provenance_role =} provenance roles below with a public page (i.e. {= url =}+ URL) that supports the role for that same holding.

Each `holder_or_source_family` is a real public source family for archive holdings: an archival holder/repository, institutional archive, archive platform, catalog or finding-aid family, digitization project, corpus provider, or comparable source ecology. It may be the same named entity as `holder` when the holder itself is the family. Different program series, item slugs, subpaths, mirror pages, uploader accounts, tag/search/list pages, or hosted-item templates inside one corpus are not distinct holder/source families unless the cited page visibly anchors a separately named repository, corpus, catalog, project, or institutional holder.

Each holding is a specific (`holder_or_source_family`, `holder`, `holding_title`) combination: the family just described; the institution, platform, repository, or archive that presents the material; and the collection, series, record set, or archive-framed item title. Collection-, series-, and record-set-level holdings are the normal unit for broad finding aids, collection guides, and corpus pages. Serialized programs, episodes, oral-history interview pages, or hosted audio items under one corpus are separate item-level holdings only when each item-specific surface has stable archival framing and materially distinct holding, access, or provenance detail for that item.

The provenance roles of interest, which we refer to as `provenance_role`, are:
- `custody_record`: a page identifying the holder, repository, platform, or archive and the named holding.
- `access_surface`: a page showing holding-specific playback, download, catalog availability, request access, on-site access, restricted access, or another public access condition for the holding.
- `provenance_context`: a page tying the holding through substantive context to a creator, broadcaster, program, date or period, Persian/Farsi language context, institution, digitization project, or collection history.

The holding ought to be a named archive collection, series, record set, or archive-framed recording, not a generic article/feed/audio category. Broadcast/radio holdings are especially natural here, but oral-history, field-recording, cultural-audio, and spoken-word holdings can count when the page frames a material Persian/Farsi recorded-audio component as archival material. A broad finding aid, collection guide, or corpus page can support the collection-, series-, or record-set-level holding that the guide is about when the page or visible section is dedicated and specific to that holding. Inventory entries, tape lines, file entries, and digital-object lines inside such a broad guide are not separate item-level archive holdings unless the cited page resolves to a stable item-specific record, URL, anchor, or visible section dedicated to that item and the item is visibly framed as an archival record/holding or as a named part of a collection, series, program, repository holding, or record set. Serial item pages from one archive, corpus, or platform are not separate holdings when the only item-level signals are a title or program number, media/player/download widgets, generic language/date/uploader metadata, a broad project description, or a host-wide collection label repeated across many pages. A platform-hosted item page, uploaded-item title, player/download surface, uploader/date block, language field, or broad platform category is not enough by itself. Generic tag, search, category, feed, or portal-list pages that merely list many recordings are not enough to establish item-level holdings. Standalone uploaded audio files, current episodes, ordinary podcast/feed entries, commercial music tracks, and random Farsi audio pages are outside scope even on archive-like platforms unless the page supplies archival or collection framing. The sources should be fully public, accessible, and usable as normal pages.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the claimed holder/source-family context, the claimed holder/platform/repository, and the named holding or a close collection/series title match.
- The page must show that the holding has a material Persian/Farsi recorded-audio component, such as Persian-language broadcast audio, a Farsi program or service, Persian oral-history recordings, or a recorded-audio collection explicitly described as Persian/Farsi.
- The page must provide the evidence appropriate to `provenance_role`: for `custody_record`, it should identify the holder/repository/platform relationship to the holding; for `access_surface`, it should show a holding-specific playback, download, catalog, request, on-site, restricted, or comparable access condition rather than only host-wide player/download boilerplate; for `provenance_context`, it should give substantive contextual provenance such as creator, broadcaster, program, date or period, language, institutional history, digitization, or collection-history detail rather than only title, serial number, uploader/date, generic tags, or repeated corpus boilerplate.
